ion: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":25,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When William de Tracy I was born about 1357, in Toddington, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom, his father, John de Tracy, was 44 and his mother, Ann Swynne, was 23. He had at least 2 sons with Alice de Baddington. He died in 1399, in his hometown, at the age of 43, and was buried in Toddington, Gloucestershire, England."},"et":{"about 1357–1399":"umbes 1357–1399","1357–1399":"1357–1399","1361–Female":"1361–Surnud","1367–Female":"1367–Surnud","1379–Male":"1379–Surnud","1379–1441":"1379–1441","1315–1379":"1315–1379","1335–1387":"1335–1387","1315":"1315","1379":"1379","1335":"1335","1357":"1357","1367":"1367","1399":"1399","1387":"1387","1441":"1441","about 1357":"umbes 1357","Bef 1379":"enne 1379","1361":"1361","1382":"1382","England":"England","Toddington, Gloucestershire, Inglaterra":"Toddington, Gloucestershire, England","Toddington, Gloucestershire, England":"Toddington, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","St Andrew Churchyard, Toddington, Gloucestershire, England":"Toddington, Gloucestershire, England"},"fi":{"about 1357–1399":"noin 1357–1399","1357–1399":"1357–1399","1361–Female":"1361–Kuollut","1367–Female":"1367–Kuollut","1379–Male":"1379–Kuollut","1379–1441":"1379–1441","1